Body: Description: Error MSG: Could not write value PlugPlayServiceType to keySystemCurrentControlSetServicesEndpoint Protector.Verify that you have suffident access tothat key,or contact your support personnel.
Invitation updated. Attendees: Marian Ilies, Amy Zhang
Invitation updated. Attendees: No attendees listed
What We've Learned Updated: Client cannot uninstall nor upgrade to a new EPP client due to the error related to the plugplay in the screenshot they've provided.
Next Steps Updated: Need to set up a remote session.

What We've Learned Updated: During the remote session I took control and used the ZAP tool to removed any remnants of the old appliance of EPP then deleted the achive + the extracted folder with SHIFT +Delete buttons.

After that we restarted the machine and tried to install a new version of EPP, and client was able to do it without a problem.
Next Steps Updated: Agreed to close the case.
